ğŸ“Œ 6. Key Agent Components (Mapped)

| Component | Present? | How           |
| --------- | -------- | ------------- |
| Input     | âœ…        | User input    |
| Rules     | âœ…        | ifâ€“else logic |
| Decision  | âœ…        | Rule matching |
| Action    | âœ…        | Response      |
| Memory    | âŒ        | Not present   |
| Learning  | âŒ        | Not present   |

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

âš ï¸ Limitations of Rule-Based Agents

* Cannot learn from experience
* Hard to scale rules
* No memory
* No reasoning
* No autonomy

ğŸ‘‰ This is **not true Agentic AI**, but the **base layer**.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ“Œ 7. How This Evolves into Agentic AI

| Stage        | Capability  |
| ------------ | ----------- |
| Rule-Based   | Fixed rules |
| Goal-Based   | Goal-driven |
| Tool-Based   | Uses APIs   |
| Memory-Based | Remembers   |
| Agentic AI   | Autonomous  |

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

âŒ Common Beginner Mistakes

* Writing too many hardcoded rules
* No default case
* No exit condition
* Treating rule-based agent as intelligent AI

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ¯ Key Takeaways

* Rule-based agents are the **starting point**
* They follow **fixed decision logic**
* Useful for understanding agent flow
* Foundation for building advanced Agentic AI agents

